Description: Do you have space to store your material things?
ChangeDescriptionText: 1|You have a small warehouse in London, down by the docks.
Name: Memoirs: A person of property

Description: One day, this will be your nation's flag. [Equip to an Auxiliary slot.]
Name: Stored A Banner of Coming Glory (London)

Description: It was the Laconic General who named the Carnelian Coast. Then she discovered it was full of sapphires. Imagine her embarrassment.
Name: Stored A Casket of Sapphires (London)

Description: A sullen viric glow leaks from within. Sometimes it rattles. Best not open it.
Name: Stored A Mirrorcatch Box Full of Very Angry Dream-Snakes (London)

Description: Death, laid out for your careful inspection.
Name: Stored Anatomical Cabinet (London)

Description: The Revenue Men have removed the most challenging elements, and applied a customs stamp to the title leaf.
Name: Stored Approved Romantic Literature (London)

Description: Who plucks the flax from the banks of rivers that flow through sleep?
Name: Stored Bale of Parabola-Linen (London)

Description:
"Like a lane of beams athwart the sea,
Thro' all the circle of the golden year!" [An effective device for seeking enemies.]
Name: Stored Blazing Glim-Lamp (London)

Description: Soft as silence.
Name: Stored Bolts of Spider-Silk (London)

Description: Devours engine emissions, ensuring that your engine never explodes at Full Power. Also slightly improves your chances of evading enemy attention.
Name: Stored Caminus Yards Avid Suppressor (London)

Description: "IT'S A MONSTER. ARE YOU?" A powerful weapon that relies on Torpedo attacks.
Name: Stored Caminus Yards 'Bandersnatch' (London)

Description: A roaring beast of an engine.
Name: Stored Caminus Yards 'Compulsion' (London)

Description: Speak not of it.
Name: Stored Caminus Yards 'D__nation' (London)

Description: "Caminus Yards: We Have Always Loved You." A powerful weapon that permits Flensing attacks.
Name: Stored Caminus Yards Heart-Ender (London)

Description: "Caminus Yards: Stand Well Back." A weapon of savage and alarming power.
Name: Stored Caminus Yards Hellthrasher (London)

Description: Get Rats Where Rats Are Required, Pneumatically. [In combat, this can deploy Rattus Faber assistants for quicker repairs.]
Name: Stored Caminus Yards Pneumatic Ratsender (London)

Description: Sealed and triple-sealed with wax.
Name: Stored Carboy of Primordial Shrieks (London)

Description: The finest output of the Greyfields shroom-yards.
Name: Stored Cask of Mushroom Wine (London)

Description: GOOD DAY. I WILL NOT CAUSE TROUBLE.
Name: Stored Clay Man, Marked for London (London)

Description: Sentiments and histories coil, prisoned by irrigo as the irrigo is prisoned by amber. Mourn the mind that has passed.
Name: Stored Colossal Fluke-Core (London)

Description: Provides some small degree of protection against excisemen searching your ship for contraband.
Name: Stored Concealed Compartment (London)

Description: Strictly speaking, this shouldn't be sold to civilian vessels at all, but the Admiralty has grown more casual of late.
Name: Stored Cotterell & Hathersage 'Admiralty Special' (London)

Description: "DON'T DO IT AGAIN." One of C&H's newer models.
Name: Stored Cotterell & Hathersage 'Denunciation' (London)

Description: A severe disincentive to pursuit.
Name: Stored Cotterell & Hathersage 'Discouragement' (London)

Description: It makes the most tremendous bang. Not what you'd call an elegant weapon, but it does make the most tremendous bang. [The Majesty is the only front-mounted pure cannon: others are torpedoes or flensing weapons.]
Name: Stored Cotterell & Hathersage 'Majesty' (London)

Description: Models No. 1 through No. 3 are not discussed in polite company, but this is a powerful and effective device.
Name: Stored Cotterell & Hathersage 'Manticore No.4' (London)

Description: This device operates in so absurd a manner as not to be easily credited. It does, nevertheless, permit torpedo attacks.
Name: Stored Cotterell & Hathersage Pneumatic Dynamite Torpedo-Gun (London)

Description: "WE SHALL COMPEL ATTENTION." A weapon of respectable power.
Name: Stored Cotterell & Hathersage 'Reproach' (London)

Description: These were poets or murderers or priests... or zee-captains. This crate bears a customs mark.
Name: Stored Crate of Brilliant Human Souls (London)

Description: Clinking, glowing, pleading.
Name: Stored Crate of Human Souls (London)

Description: The nature of these yellowish morsels is unclear, except that they are unlikely to be composed of deceased devils. They are kept in sealed cannisters, possibly as ammunition.
Name: Stored Devilbone Dice (London)

Description: It has claws; it has a fierce double beak; but just now it seems disinclined to use them.
Name: Stored Docile Blemmigan (London)

Description:
'The Monster-Hunter winnows the lesser terrors from the true. She has slain That Which Makes Light in the Deeps, eaten its flesh in remembrance of certain Feasts of the Zee, and fashioned her weapon from its remains. She was human, once.' 
But this Monster-Hunter is ready for a glorious ending. Icarus in Black awaits.
Name: Stored Doomed Monster-Hunter (London)

Description: A battered, rusting mechanism that will ensure your ship goes in more or less the correct direction.
Name: Stored Elderly Steeple-Engine (London)

Description: And yet it moves. A piece, emission or work of the Dawn Machine.
Name: Stored Element of Dawn (London)

Description: A chest with an embedded matrix of mirrors: an unlikely device for capturing sunlight.
Name: Stored Empty Mirrorcatch Box (London)

Description: A hundred dreams in every barrel.
Name: Stored Firkin of Prisoner's Honey (London)

Description: Flares may be used to reveal your enemies, increasing the speed of your firing solution.
Name: Stored Flare (London)

Description: We've all made mistakes. If only those mistakes could be left in the dark.
Name: Stored Foxfire Candles (London)

Description: Coal, dug from zee-cliffs or imported from Hell. [If you run out of fuel, you will drift helplessly.]
Name: Stored Fuel (London)

Description: A bucket of tiny but razor-toothed serpentlings.
Name: Stored Harlot-Fry (London)

Description: This desperate, demented device inflicts apocalyptic damage on even the greatest zee-beasts, but it fires only one thing: Monster-Hunters. [You may find them in the Chelonate and Khan's Shadow, and occasionally elsewhere.]
Name: Stored Icarus in Black (London)

Description: Be sure their sins will find them out. [The Judgement Resonator does not limit your ability to hide.]
Name: Stored Judgement Resonator (London)

Description: "THE BOADICEA: MORE POWER, LESS SUBTLETY." The best Leadbeater & Stainrod can supply, although as usual they've skimped on materials.
Name: Stored Leadbeater & Stainrod 'Boadicea' (London)

Description: "Fear her touch!" One of L&S' more reliable pieces, which isn't saying much. Permits Flensing attacks.
Name: Stored Leadbeater & Stainrod 'Britomart' Flensing-Cannon (London)

Description: The 'Illyrian' is an outdated model, but it'll get you where you need to go.
Name: Stored Leadbeater & Stainrod 'Illyrian' (London)

Description: "THIS WAY UP." A weapon which may serve against small monsters or feeble pirates.
Name: Stored Leadbeater & Stainrod Reconditioned Frigate-Surplus Deck-Gun Mark II (London)

Description: A sting in your tail.
Name: Stored Leadbeater & Stainrod 'Scorpion' (London)

Description: 'Seaworm' torpedoes are small but lethal. Don't underestimate them.
Name: Stored Leadbeater & Stainrod 'Seaworm' (London)

Description: "WINNOW THE SLUMBERING GREEN!" Permits Torpedo attacks.
Name: Stored Leadbeater & Stainrod 'Winnower' (London)

Description: Something wriggling and peculiar. It's safely confined, probably.
Name: Stored Live Specimen (London)

Description: "Omnia mors perimit et nulli miseretur"
Name: Stored Memento Mori (London)

Description: This frankly sinister device reduces the amount of fuel that an engine uses. It also really frightens the crew. Apparently, that's necessary.
Name: Stored Milebreaker (London)

Description: A stack of notebooks, closely written in treasure-ink.
Name: Stored Monstrous Almanac (London)

Description: Get back. Get back! Don't look at it directly!
Name: Stored Montaigne Projector (London)

Description: Tastes like clean air and crystallised ginger. Also has the interesting property of paralysing the vocal chords if you sprinkle it in your stew.
Name: Stored Mutersalt (London)

Description: You have confined this unfortunate to a cage in the hold. [Prisoners survive on scraps and do not usually require Supplies. Release your Prisoner by using this item, or take them back to London for other purposes...]
Name: Stored Prisoner (London)

Description: All the adventures of the heart are here, in prose, poetry or pictorial form. Some may be more suitable for private consumption. [Note: in London, customs duty is paid on love stories. Even illustrated love stories.]
Name: Stored Romantic Literature (London)

Description: All the fire of Hell, and all the aroma of Heaven.
Name: Stored Sack of Darkdrop Coffee Beans (London)

Description: Coral that glimmers as if moonlit. It makes marvellous jewellery or terribly expensive tea.
Name: Stored Scintillack (London)

Description: Ensure that no-one gets in without the key. In... or out.[This will help protect against acquisitive passengers and over-lively cargo.]
Name: Stored Secure Compartment (London)

Description: Look how it glides. Like moonlight.
Name: Stored Serene Aquarium (London)

Description: A kind of glory.
Name: Stored Shining Knight (London)

Description: A glittering altar carved with the Signs of the South.
Name: Stored Shrine to Stone (London)

Description: A Miraculous New Process Enables Passage Through Eternal Night! Do Not Consume.  [An adequate device for seeking enemies.]
Name: Stored Soft Glim-Lamp (London)

Description: On first sight, it looks like a tomb-colonist coffin. On closer examination, it carries stencilling reading SOOTHE & COOPER and a handwritten tag: 'DELIVERY TO DEPOT (A), STATION III'.
Name: Stored Soothe & Cooper Long-Box (London)

Description: Speculative Consonance: less than a technique, more than just a theory. [The Consonator does not limit your ability to hide.]
Name: Stored Speculative Consonator (London)

Description: The Unmakers have smashed these sad and rubbly remnants off the flanks of a Salt Lion. A contact in London will purchase them.
Name: Stored Sphinxstone (London)

Description: "AN INESCAPABLE ENDING!" A potent weapon which permits Flensing attacks.
Name: Stored Stampshod's 'Calvary' Prong Launcher (London)

Description: It might be some sort of fish, but best not to look too closely.
Name: Stored Strange Catch (London)

Description: The black bones of zee-monsters make for startling corsets.
Name: Stored Stygian Ivory (London)

Description: It's very dangerous, but who cares when it's so pretty?
Name: Stored Sunlight-Filled Mirrorcatch Box (London)

Description: Food and equipment. [If you run out of supplies, Hunger will eventually destroy you.]
Name: Stored Supplies (London)

Description: This weird skull once adorned the worm-drawn priest-barge of the Chelonate.
Name: Stored The Figurehead of the Eater of Names (London)

Description: "These are the forces that drive the Bazaar." The Impeller runs very, very hot.
Name: Stored The Fulgent Impeller (London)

Description: A shimmering complexus of steel and glass. In its heart, a serpent-king rages. Or so the Magician claims.
Name: Stored The Serpentine (London)

Description: Technically, passengers rather than goods. But you'd never know it to talk to them. [They'll pay their passage to the Tomb-Colonies: sell them there.]
Name: Stored Tomb-Colonist (London)

Description: Deploy these in combat for unparalleled protection against torpedoes!
Name: Stored Torpedo Nets (London)

Description: They make these on the roof-tops, and won't say why. [A one-use item that will remove all Illumination from both sides in combat, and increase Terror.]
Name: Stored Unclear Device (London)

Description: A crate of exceptional human souls. It has never known the tender touch of the Imperial Customs stamp. Consequently, it cannot be sold on the open market, and you'd better not be caught with it.
Name: Stored Unstamped Crate of Brilliant Souls (London)

Description: A crate of pleading souls. This one does not bear a customs stamp - it is contraband!
Name: Stored Unstamped Crate of Human Souls (London)

Description: Its eyes glitter with awareness. Its melancholy has dissipated: now you sense anticipation.
Name: Stored Wakeful Idol (London)

Description: A sinister little squatting image... but its eyes are pleading.
Name: Stored Watchful Curio (London)

Description: WE WILL WORK. WE WILL ONLY WORK. [This trio of Clay stokers will reduce crew requirements, but also crew capacity, and will slightly increase engine power. They are fitted to an Auxiliary slot. When they are not in use, they will stand, patiently, hands by their sides, flat grey eyes unreadable. One will say, sometimes: "I LIKE IT WHEN IT IS QUIET."]
Name: Stored WE ARE CLAY (London)

Description: "Oh yes, the Drowned Man is humming tonight, a song in the water like the bones of fish."
Name: Stored Whispering Trophy-Case (London)

Description: Glass as clear as ice and sharp as salt.
Name: Stored Whithern Optical (London)

Description: The colour: old blood on snow. The taste: paprika, mushrooms, irony. The recipe: closely guarded.
Name: Stored Zzoup (London)
